Below is a **self-contained, vanilla-JS snippet** that injects a floating WhatsApp button into any page.  
Copy-paste it just before the closing `</body>` tag (or run it after the DOM is ready) and you’re done—no external libraries required.

```html
<!-- WhatsApp floating button (transparent background) -->
<script>
(() => {
  /* ---------- Configuration ---------- */
  const WA_TARGET_URL = "https://web.whatsapp.com/";       // or e.g. "https://wa.me/6591234567"
  const SIZE          = 64;                                // diameter in px
  const OFFSET        = 20;                                // distance from viewport edges in px
  const EXPAND_RATIO  = 1.15;                              // how much bigger on click
  const ANIM_MS       = 160;                               // click animation duration

  /* ---------- Create the button ---------- */
  const btn = document.createElement("button");
  btn.type  = "button";
  btn.id    = "wa-fab";
  btn.ariaLabel = "Open WhatsApp Web";

  /* Inline SVG icon — keeps background transparent */
  btn.innerHTML = `
    <svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" width="100%" height="100%" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
      <path fill="#25d366" d="M16.004 2.001A14.005 14.005 0 0 0 2 16.006c0 2.468.64 4.781 1.852 6.85L2 30l7.355-1.82A13.922 13.922 0 0 0 16.004 30 14.005 14.005 0 0 0 30 16.006 14.005 14.005 0 0 0 16.004 2.001zm0 2.003a11.999 11.999 0 0 1 11.999 12.002 11.999 11.999 0 0 1-11.999 12.002 11.902 11.902 0 0 1-5.499-1.409l-.393-.221-4.371 1.084 1.14-4.264-.23-.404A11.897 11.897 0 0 1 4.002 16.006 11.999 11.999 0 0 1 16.004 4.004zm-4.365 7.088-.315 1.071c-.23.774.096 1.51.769 2.185 1.391 1.396 2.81 3.114 4.859 4.019.63.282 1.305.437 1.998.437.499 0 1.03-.098 1.638-.282l1.023-.313c.576-.177.961-.561 1.098-1.055l.492-1.79c.1-.366.013-.742-.24-1.05l-2.003-2.449c-.356-.431-.876-.546-1.37-.357l-1.616.601c-.222.085-.386.24-.466.424l-.482 1.089a.247.247 0 0 1-.233.145c-.052 0-.106-.009-.162-.03-.835-.323-1.47-.72-2.06-1.315-.59-.595-.986-1.23-1.308-2.068-.043-.115-.046-.226-.008-.312l.488-1.121c.161-.369.049-.804-.268-1.144l-2.043-2.22c-.259-.281-.666-.372-1.036-.249l-1.709.564a1.3 1.3 0 0 0-.861.89z"/>
    </svg>`;

  /* ---------- Style it (JS-injected CSS) ---------- */
  Object.assign(btn.style, {
    position:   "fixed",
    bottom:     `${OFFSET}px`,
    right:      `${OFFSET}px`,
    width:      `${SIZE}px`,
    height:     `${SIZE}px`,
    padding:    "0",
    border:     "none",
    borderRadius:"50%",
    background: "transparent",
    cursor:     "pointer",
    outline:    "none",
    zIndex:     1000,
    transition: `transform ${ANIM_MS}ms ease-in-out`,
  });

  /* ---------- Click behaviour ---------- */
  btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    // visual feedback (scale up briefly)
    btn.style.transform = `scale(${EXPAND_RATIO})`;
    setTimeout(() => { btn.style.transform = "scale(1)"; }, ANIM_MS);

    // open WhatsApp Web in a new tab
    window.open(WA_TARGET_URL, "_blank", "noopener,noreferrer");
  });

  /* ---------- Inject into document ---------- */
  document.body.appendChild(btn);
})();
</script>
```

### How it works
| Step | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| **1 – Config block** | Change `WA_TARGET_URL`, size, offset, and animation constants without touching the rest of the code. |
| **2 – Create button** | A `<button>` element is built with an inline SVG logo so the **background remains fully transparent**. |
| **3 – Apply styles** | All CSS is injected via `Object.assign`, making the snippet portable—no external stylesheet needed. The button is fixed at the bottom-right, above most page elements (`z-index: 1000`). |
| **4 – Click listener** | On click the element scales up (`transform: scale(1.15)`) for tactile feedback, then immediately opens WhatsApp Web in a **new, sandboxed tab** (`noopener,noreferrer`). |
| **5 – Inject** | The script runs immediately, appending the button to `document.body`. No frameworks or build steps required. |

Feel free to swap in your own SVG, adjust colours, or replace the target URL with a phone-number deep link (e.g. `https://wa.me/<countryCode><number>`).

