Below is the **drop-in replacement** that uses the *official* WhatsApp brand icon (transparent PNG taken from WhatsApp’s own asset set) instead of the rough inline SVG.

```html
<!-- Floating WhatsApp button (official icon, transparent BG) -->
<script>
(() => {
  /* ====== CONFIG ====== */
  const WA_URL       = "https://web.whatsapp.com/";                   // page to open
  const ICON_URL     = "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5e/WhatsApp_icon.png"; // official 512 × 512 PNGciteturn0search8
  const SIZE         = 64;     // ⌀ in px
  const OFFSET       = 20;     // distance from bottom-right in px
  const EXPAND_SCALE = 1.15;   // growth on click (15 %)
  const ANIM_MS      = 160;    // click feedback duration

  /* ====== CREATE BUTTON ====== */
  const btn = document.createElement("button");
  btn.type        = "button";
  btn.id          = "wa-fab";
  btn.ariaLabel   = "Open WhatsApp Web";
  btn.style.cssText = `
      position:fixed; bottom:${OFFSET}px; right:${OFFSET}px;
      width:${SIZE}px; height:${SIZE}px;
      padding:0; border:none; border-radius:50%;
      background:transparent; cursor:pointer; outline:none;
      z-index:1000; transition:transform ${ANIM_MS}ms ease-in-out;
  `;

  /* add the *official* icon inside */
  const img = new Image();
  img.src   = ICON_URL;
  img.alt   = "";
  img.style.cssText = "width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:contain;pointer-events:none;";
  btn.appendChild(img);

  /* ====== BEHAVIOUR ====== */
  btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    btn.style.transform = `scale(${EXPAND_SCALE})`;
    setTimeout(() => btn.style.transform = "scale(1)", ANIM_MS);
    window.open(WA_URL, "_blank", "noopener,noreferrer");
  });

  document.body.appendChild(btn);
})();
</script>
```

### Why this version is “standard”

* **Icon fidelity** – The PNG at 512 × 512 px is WhatsApp’s official roundel asset and scales cleanly down to 64 px with no aliasing or distortion.citeturn0search8  
* **Transparent surroundings** – Only the green circle + white phone are visible; the button itself has no background colour, so it sits well on any page.  
* **Click feedback** – `transform: scale()` gives a subtle tactile cue (15 % growth for 160 ms) without affecting layout.  
* **No dependencies** – Everything runs in vanilla JS; CSS is injected inline, so you can paste this near `</body>` and forget about it.  

Feel free to swap `WA_URL` for a *wa.me* deep-link (`https://wa.me/<countrycode><number>`) if you want to jump straight into a chat.

Below is an updated **drop-in script** that gives a crisper “pop” effect on click while the button background stays absolutely transparent.

```html
