  const WA_URL       = "https://web.whatsapp.com/";                         // or https://wa.me/<number>
  const ICON_URL     = "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5e/WhatsApp_icon.png"; // 512-px official PNG
  const SIZE         = 64;          // normal diameter in px
  const OFFSET       = 20;          // distance from bottom-right in px
  const SCALE_UP     = 1.25;        // how much bigger on press (1.25 ⇒ +25 %)
  const ANIM_MS      = 180;         // duration of the pop animation (ms)

  /* ========= CREATE BUTTON ========= */
  const btn = document.createElement("button");
  btn.type      = "button";
  btn.ariaLabel = "Open WhatsApp Web";

  /* base style – keep background fully transparent */
  btn.style.cssText = `
    position:fixed; bottom:${OFFSET}px; right:${OFFSET}px;
    width:${SIZE}px; height:${SIZE}px;
    padding:0; border:none; border-radius:50%;
    background:transparent; cursor:pointer; outline:none;
    z-index:1000; transition:transform ${ANIM_MS}ms ease-out;
  `;

  /* icon */
  const img = new Image();
  img.src = ICON_URL;
  img.alt = "";
  img.style.cssText = `
    width:100%; height:100%; object-fit:contain;
    pointer-events:none;       /* icon shouldn’t intercept clicks */
  `;
  btn.appendChild(img);

  /* ========= ANIMATION & LINK ========= */
  const pop = () => {
    btn.style.transform = `scale(${SCALE_UP})`;
    setTimeout(() => { btn.style.transform = "scale(1)"; }, ANIM_MS);
  };

  btn.addEventListener("pointerdown", pop);        // immediate feedback as finger/mouse goes down
  btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    window.open(WA_URL, "_blank", "noopener,noreferrer"); // open in new tab
  });

  document.body.appendChild(btn);
})();
</script>
```

### What changed & why it’s clearer

| Improvement | Detail |
|-------------|--------|
| **Pointer-down trigger** | The scale-up now starts on `pointerdown`, so the effect happens the moment the user presses, not after the click finishes. |
| **Bigger pop (`scale 1.25`)** | A 25 % growth is usually noticeable even on retina/Hi-DPI screens. |
| **Short ease-out animation** | `ease-out` feels snappy: it grows fast, then settles back smoothly. |
| **Still 100 % transparent** | The button element has *no background fill*; only the PNG inside is visible. |

Feel free to tweak `SCALE_UP`, `ANIM_MS`, or swap `WA_URL` for a `wa.me` deep-link to jump straight into a chat.

Below is a **single, self-contained script** that

* shows the *official* WhatsApp icon with a transparent background  
* **hovers** with a gentle glow + slight scale-up  
* **pops** a bit more on press / click (then opens WhatsApp Web in a new tab)  
* keeps all styling and logic in the snippet—no external CSS or libraries needed.

```html
<!-- Floating WhatsApp button — hover + press effects (transparent BG) -->
<script>
(() => {
  /* ========= CONFIG ========= */
  const WA_URL       = "https://web.whatsapp.com/";                         // or e.g. https://wa.me/6591234567
  const ICON_URL     = "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5e/WhatsApp_icon.png"; // official PNG
  const SIZE         = 64;          // diameter (px)
  const OFFSET       = 20;          // distance from bottom-right (px)
  const HOVER_SCALE  = 1.12;        // scale on hover
  const PRESS_SCALE  = 1.25;        // scale on press
  const ANIM_MS      = 180;         // press animation duration (ms)

  /* ========= CREATE BUTTON ========= */
  const btn = document.createElement("button");
  btn.type      = "button";
  btn.id        = "wa-fab";
  btn.ariaLabel = "Open WhatsApp Web";

  // base inline style (keeps background fully transparent)
  btn.style.cssText = `
    position:fixed; bottom:${OFFSET}px; right:${OFFSET}px;
    width:${SIZE}px; height:${SIZE}px;
    padding:0; border:none; border-radius:50%;
    background:transparent; cursor:pointer; outline:none;
    z-index:1000; transition:transform ${ANIM_MS}ms ease-out,
                             filter    ${ANIM_MS}ms ease-out;
  `;

  // icon
  const img = new Image();
  img.src = ICON_URL;
  img.alt = "";
  img.style.cssText = `
    width:100%; height:100%; object-fit:contain;
    pointer-events:none;                /* icon shouldn’t intercept clicks */
  `;
  btn.appendChild(img);

  /* ========= HOVER STYLES (via injected CSS) ========= */
  const css = document.createElement("style");
  css.textContent = `
    #wa-fab:hover {
      transform: scale(${HOVER_SCALE});
      filter: drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(37,211,102,.65));
    }
  `;
  document.head.appendChild(css);

  /* ========= PRESS / CLICK BEHAVIOUR ========= */
  btn.addEventListener("pointerdown", () => {
    // immediate tactile pop
    btn.style.transform = \`scale(${PRESS_SCALE})\`;
    setTimeout(() => btn.style.removeProperty("transform"), ANIM_MS);
  });

  btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
    window.open(WA_URL, "_blank", "noopener,noreferrer");
  });

  document.body.appendChild(btn);
})();
</script>
```

### How it works

| Event | Visual feedback | Why it stays transparent |
|-------|-----------------|--------------------------|
| **Hover** | Scales to 112 % and gets a soft green glow (`drop-shadow`). | Background is never altered—only the icon and shadow render. |
| **Press/Click** | Instantly scales to 125 %, then snaps back after 180 ms. | The `pointerdown` handler sets an *inline* transform that overrides the hover rule; the `setTimeout` removes it so the hover state (if still hovered) resumes. |
| **Release** | If still hovered, button shows the hover glow; otherwise it’s back to normal. | No residual inline transforms, so the normal/hover CSS rules take over. |

Tweak `HOVER_SCALE`, `PRESS_SCALE`, or `ANIM_MS` to taste, or swap `WA_URL` for a direct `wa.me` deep-link.

